race.comment: A tight-knit handicap where just 1kg in the weights separates top and bottom. CAPTAIN PARMA (11) won  over course and distance before a good second behind HE'S A GENTLEMAN (2) at Wolverhampton last month. Might be capable of reversing placings back at this venue receiving a good draw. The latter has gone up 1kg and can remain competitive once more although the bigger danger might come from STAR OF MALI (10) who always looked in command when winning tackling track and trip four weeks ago. BEAUTY CHOICE (3) was denied a neck over 1200m at Catterick and will have no problem returning to the AW as a four-time winner on the surface.
